---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import TrustBlock from "../components/TrustBlock.astro";
import FoundingCTA from "../components/FoundingCTA.astro";
import PricingBadge from "../components/PricingBadge.astro";

const title = "IT Project Recovery | Ascend Griffin";
const description =
  "Structured recovery for an IT project that lost momentum. Restore delivery rhythm, re-paper vendor agreements, a clear plan for what's next. From $2,500/month.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="about">
    <section class="hero hero-bg-media" style="--hero-img:url('/img/rescue.webp')">
      <div class="about-shell">
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">01 · Recovery</p>

        <h1 class="hero-h1">
          Bring the project <em>back on course</em>.
        </h1>

        <p class="hero-lede">
          Project lost momentum. Vendor unresponsive. Budget draining without visible progress. Before you fire the team, rebuild from scratch, or write off the spend — a structured recovery with a clear plan for what comes next.
        </p>

        <PricingBadge price="from $2,500" duration="monthly retainer" unit="/month" />

        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a
            href="#book"
            class="btn-primary"
            data-modal="booking"
            data-subject="support"
            data-source="recovery-hero"
          >
            Book Discovery Call →
          </a>
          <a href="#how" class="btn-ghost">See how it works →</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <TrustBlock />

    <section class="acc-section">
      <div class="about-shell">
        <details class="acc" name="rescue" id="who">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">02</span>
            <span class="acc-label">Who this is for</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <h3 class="acc-h">Three typical situations I work with.</h3>
            <p class="acc-lede">Each starts looking like a different problem but ends with the same need: someone reads the situation honestly and proposes a workable plan.</p>

            <article class="icp-card">
              <header class="icp-header">
                <span class="icp-letter">A</span>
                <h4 class="icp-title">The vendor has gone quiet.</h4>
              </header>
              <p>Calls get rescheduled. Updates come less often. The Slack channel where work used to happen has slowly gone silent. Maybe the team is overloaded; maybe your project lost priority; maybe a key developer left. Either way — response is slower than you need, and the spend keeps running. <em>First job: honestly figure out whether the relationship can be repaired, or whether it should end cleanly.</em></p>
            </article>

            <article class="icp-card">
              <header class="icp-header">
                <span class="icp-letter">B</span>
                <h4 class="icp-title">Scope expands, outcome doesn't.</h4>
              </header>
              <p>Started at $40K. Now at $80K with the original feature list still incomplete. Every change request lands with another "this will need two more weeks." You can't tell whether it's legitimate re-scope or just stretching the project. <em>First job: separate real scope changes from padding, re-paper the agreement on transparent terms, restore progress against milestones.</em></p>
            </article>

            <article class="icp-card">
              <header class="icp-header">
                <span class="icp-letter">C</span>
                <h4 class="icp-title">The team is working but delivery has stopped.</h4>
              </header>
              <p>People are engaged. Standups happen. Sprint reviews show movement. But the actual shipping has halted — and nobody inside the team can name why. <em>First job: read the situation from outside the politics — process, scope, technical assumptions — and surface the real blocker without damaging the relationship.</em></p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="acc" name="rescue" id="how">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">03</span>
            <span class="acc-label">How it works</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <h3 class="acc-h">What you get at each phase.</h3>
            <p class="acc-lede">Work runs in phases. Each one ends with a concrete decision you can make based on real data.</p>

            <ol class="modes">
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">01</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>Diagnostic (weeks 1-2).</h4>
                  <p>Read the codebase, the vendor contract, the comms history; interview the team. Identify what's actually broken versus what's just symptomatic. End-of-phase artifact: a one-page recovery plan you can show co-founders, investors, or board.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">02</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>Stabilize (weeks 3-8).</h4>
                  <p>Either re-paper the vendor agreement on transparent terms, or close it cleanly. Restore weekly delivery cadence. Triage technical debt — what we fix, what we live with, what we plan around. End-of-phase: predictable shipping resumed, financial bleed stopped.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">03</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>Hand-off (week 8+).</h4>
                  <p>One of two paths. Either the project is stable with the existing team and I step out, leaving documentation and a clear next step. Or we transition to a vetted team from the network with structured handover. Either way, the project runs without me in the room.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>

            <div class="outcomes">
              <p class="outcomes-h">The end value isn't the plan itself — it's what the plan unlocks:</p>
              <ul class="outcomes-list">
                <li>Restore delivery rhythm — predictable weekly progress you can show investors or team.</li>
                <li>Stop financial losses on misaligned decisions — renegotiated terms, honest milestones, transparent spend.</li>
                <li>Finish the project with a working outcome — either with you, or with a new team from the network.</li>
                <li>Or make the honest call to stop — with minimal losses and a clear plan for what to do with existing code and data.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="acc" name="rescue" id="not-included">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">04</span>
            <span class="acc-label">Not included</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <h3 class="acc-h">What recovery <em>isn't</em>.</h3>

            <ul class="exclude">
              <li>
                <span class="exclude-mark">→</span>
                <span><strong>Engineering management replacement.</strong> I read the project, align the plan, run process — but I'm not running developers day-to-day. If you need a fractional eng manager, that's a different format.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="exclude-mark">→</span>
                <span><strong>Hands-on code refactor.</strong> I don't rewrite production code. I tell you what needs rewriting, by whom, and in what priority.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="exclude-mark">→</span>
                <span><strong>"Just fire the vendor."</strong> Sometimes that's the answer. Often it's cheaper to renegotiate. An independent voice is needed exactly to call which path is actually realistic.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="exclude-mark">→</span>
                <span><strong>A guaranteed rescue at any cost.</strong> Some projects are better ended honestly than dragged on. That's part of the value too — and I'll say so directly if that's your situation.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="acc" name="rescue" id="faq">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">05</span>
            <span class="acc-label">Common questions</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <div class="qa">
              <h4 class="qa-q">How is this different from hiring a new team?</h4>
              <p>A new team solves "who writes the code." Recovery solves "what actually needs doing, and why isn't the project moving." Often the first step reveals the team isn't the problem — scope, agreement, or process is. In that case a new team will just repeat the same situation 3 months later.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="qa">
              <h4 class="qa-q">What if the project can't be recovered?</h4>
              <p>That's an honest answer, and I'll give it directly. Then work shifts to: cleanly closing current agreements with minimal losses; salvaging what's worth keeping (data, parts of the codebase, market learnings); and a plan for what to do with the remaining budget. Better to make that call in week 5 than spend another 4 months on something that won't fly.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="qa">
              <h4 class="qa-q">How long before things stabilize?</h4>
              <p>First useful effect — end of phase 1 (week 2): you have a plan and an honest picture. Real delivery stabilization — phase 2 (weeks 3-8), depending on the depth of the problem. Deeply distressed projects take longer; an honest forecast comes after diagnostic.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <FoundingCTA service="rescue" />
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <script>
    (function () {
      const NAME = "rescue";

      function openAccordionFromHash(hash: string | null) {
        if (!hash || hash === "#" || hash === "#book") return;
        let target: HTMLElement | null = null;
        try { target = document.querySelector(hash); } catch { return; }
        if (target && target instanceof HTMLDetailsElement && target.getAttribute("name") === NAME) {
          if (!target.open) target.open = true;
        }
      }

      function init() {
        const items = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLDetailsElement>(`details[name="${NAME}"]`);
        if (!items.length) return;
        const STICKY_OFFSET = 88;

        items.forEach((det) => {
          det.addEventListener("toggle", () => {
            if (!det.open) return;
            const summary = det.querySelector("summary");
            if (!summary) return;
            requestAnimationFrame(() => {
              requestAnimationFrame(() => {
                const rect = summary.getBoundingClientRect();
                window.scrollTo({ top: window.scrollY + rect.top - STICKY_OFFSET, behavior: "smooth" });
              });
            });
          });
        });

        document.querySelectorAll<HTMLAnchorElement>('a[href^="#"]').forEach((link) => {
          const href = link.getAttribute("href");
          if (!href || href === "#" || href === "#book") return;
          link.addEventListener("click", () => {
            openAccordionFromHash(href);
          });
        });

        openAccordionFromHash(location.hash);
      }

      if (document.readyState === "loading") {
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", init);
      } else {
        init();
      }
    })();
  </script>

  <script
    type="application/ld+json"
    set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      name: "IT Project Recovery",
      provider: { "@type": "Person", name: "Taras Smaliukh", url: "https://ascendgriffin.org/about/" },
      areaServed: ["Ukraine", "United Kingdom", "Germany", "United States"],
      description,
      offers: {
        "@type": "Offer",
        priceCurrency: "USD",
        price: "2500",
        priceSpecification: { "@type": "UnitPriceSpecification", minPrice: 2500, priceCurrency: "USD", unitText: "MONTH" },
      },
      serviceType: "IT project recovery and oversight",
    })}
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top right, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.04), transparent 50%), radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom left, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.03), transparent 40%), var(--bg-0); min-height: 100vh; }
  .about-shell { max-width: 880px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--gutter); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .about-shell { padding: 0 var(--gutter-sm); } }
  .hero { padding: 96px 0 48px; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .hero { padding: 56px 0 32px; } }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-pressed); margin: 0 0 24px; font-weight: 600; }
  .hero-h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(44px, 6vw, 76px); line-height: 1.02; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 28px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 16ch; }
  .hero-h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); font-weight: 700; }
  .hero-lede { font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 24px; max-width: 60ch; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; align-items: center; margin: 16px 0 24px; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--bg-ink); color: var(--text-on-ink); padding: 16px 28px; border-radius: 2px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: 0.02em; transition: background var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: #2a2724; }
  .btn-ghost { color: var(--text-1); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent); padding-bottom: 2px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .btn-ghost:hover { color: var(--accent-pressed); }
  .hero-hint { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin: 24px 0 0; }

  .hero-media { margin: 24px 0 0; }
  .hero-media img { display: block; width: 100%; max-height: 340px; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 10px; border: 1px solid var(--border-1); box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .hero-media img { max-height: 220px; } }

  .acc-section { padding: 16px 0 40px; }
  .acc { border-top: 1px solid var(--border-2); transition: background var(--dur-base) var(--ease); }
  .acc:last-of-type { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-2); }
  .acc[open] { background: var(--bg-1); border-top-color: var(--text-1); }
  .acc[open] + .acc { border-top-color: var(--text-1); }
  .acc-summary { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr 32px; align-items: center; gap: 16px; padding: 24px 0; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; user-select: none; }
  .acc-summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .acc-summary:hover .acc-label { color: var(--accent-pressed); }
  .acc-summary:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: 2px; border-radius: 2px; }
  .acc-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent-pressed); letter-spacing: 0.04em; line-height: 1; }
  .acc-label { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px); color: var(--text-1); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.01em; font-weight: 700; transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .acc[open] .acc-label { color: var(--editorial); }
  .acc-toggle { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 28px; color: var(--accent-pressed); line-height: 1; text-align: right; transition: transform var(--dur-base) var(--ease); font-weight: 300; }
  .acc[open] .acc-toggle { transform: rotate(45deg); }
  .acc-body { padding: 0 0 36px 72px; max-width: 68ch; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .acc-body { padding: 0 0 28px 0; } }
  .acc-h { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(22px, 2.6vw, 28px); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 20px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 24ch; }
  .acc-h em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); }
  .acc-body p { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 18px; }
  .acc-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .acc-body p strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 700; }
  .acc-body p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--text-1); }
  .acc-lede { font-size: 17px; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 28px; }

  .icp-card { margin-bottom: 28px; padding-bottom: 22px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); }
  .icp-card:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; border-bottom: 0; }
  .icp-header { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 14px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .icp-letter { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; background: var(--accent-subtle); padding: 3px 8px; border-radius: 2px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .icp-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(18px, 2.2vw, 22px); line-height: 1.25; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0; font-weight: 600; }

  .modes { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-2); }
  .mode { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr; gap: 20px; padding: 24px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); align-items: start; }
  .mode:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .mode-letter { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 18px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .mode-body h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 8px; line-height: 1.35; font-weight: 700; }
  .mode-body p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0; max-width: 60ch; }

  .outcomes { margin-top: 32px; padding: 24px 28px; background: var(--bg-0); border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); border-radius: 0 2px 2px 0; }
  .outcomes-h { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 14px; line-height: 1.45; }
  .outcomes-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .outcomes-list li { position: relative; padding: 6px 0 6px 22px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--text-2); }
  .outcomes-list li::before { content: "→"; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 6px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 700; }

  .exclude { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .exclude li { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 16px; padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border-1); color: var(--text-2); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .exclude li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .exclude-mark { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent-pressed); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; font-weight: 700; }
  .exclude strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 700; }

  .qa { margin-bottom: 28px; padding-bottom: 22px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); }
  .qa:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; border-bottom: 0; }
  .qa-q { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 10px; line-height: 1.35; font-weight: 600; }
</style>
